CatDescriptText: Columbus Couch, 1421 Sandusky Street, Democrat, 22nd Ward, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 7, 1957, pg. 3 with question: "Who is your Ward Chairman? Does he have any power? Does he exert it?" Answer reads: "I don't know who the ward chairman is, and therefore don't know whether or not he or she has any power.  However, if the ward chairman has anything to do with the appearance of and the condition of the neighborhood, I would say that everything looks lie it's in good shape and the ward chairman is doing a good job."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Columbus Couch wearing  light colored shirt and cap, holding paper bag, posed in front of brick building
